DAY 15: MAP
EXPLANATION:
  Map is a data structure for storing key-value pairs (like objects, but different).
  
  CREATING MAPS:
    const map = new Map();
    const map = new Map([
      ["name", "John"],
      ["age", 30]
    ]);
  
  ADDING/GETTING VALUES:
    map.set("name", "John");     // add key-value pair
    map.get("name");             // "John"
    map.has("name");             // true
    map.delete("name");          // removes key
    map.clear();                 // empties map
  
  PROPERTIES:
    map.size;                    // number of entries
  
  ITERATING MAPS:
    // forEach
    map.forEach((value, key) => {
      console.log(key, value);
    });
    
    // for...of
    for (let [key, value] of map) {
      console.log(key, value);
    }
  
  MAP VS OBJECT:
    Map advantages:
    - Keys can be any type (objects can only have string/symbol keys)
    - Has .size property
    - Better performance for frequent additions/deletions
    - Can iterate in insertion order
    
    Object advantages:
    - Simpler syntax
    - Can access properties with dot notation
    - Better for simple data structures

