DAY 18: TEMPORAL DEAD ZONE (CRITICAL DEEP DIVE)
EXPLANATION:
  Temporal Dead Zone is a period where let/const variables cannot be accessed.
  
  BEHAVIOR WITH LET/CONST:
    console.log(x); // ReferenceError: x is not defined
    let x = 5;
    console.log(x); // 5
    
    The area from start of block to 'let x' is the Temporal Dead Zone.
  
  BEHAVIOR WITH VAR:
    console.log(x); // undefined (not error!)
    var x = 5;
    console.log(x); // 5
  
  IN LOOPS:
    for (let i = 0; i < 5; i++) {
      console.log(i); // works, i is in scope
    }
    console.log(i); // ReferenceError - i is in TDZ outside loop
  
  WITH DEFAULT PARAMETERS:
    const x = 1;
    function test(a = x) {  // x is in TDZ here (ReferenceError if x not defined before)
      console.log(a);
    }
  
  WHY THIS MATTERS:
    - Catches mistakes (using variables before declaring)
    - Forces good coding practices
    - Different from var which has undefined
    - TDZ helps debug issues earlier

