DAY 27: DOM ADVANCED
EXPLANATION:
  Building on Day 14's basics, more complex DOM interactions.
  
  EVENT DELEGATION:
    Problem: Adding event listeners to many elements is slow
    Solution: Listen on parent, check which child was clicked
    
    // Old way (inefficient)
    document.querySelectorAll(".button").forEach(btn => {
      btn.addEventListener("click", handleClick);
    });
    
    // Better way (event delegation)
    document.addEventListener("click", (event) => {
      if (event.target.matches(".button")) {
        handleClick(event);
      }
    });
  
  EVENT OBJECT:
    element.addEventListener("click", (event) => {
      event.target;        // element that triggered event
      event.currentTarget; // element with listener
      event.type;          // "click", "mouseover", etc.
      event.preventDefault(); // stop default behavior
      event.stopPropagation(); // stop event bubbling
    });
  
  EVENT BUBBLING & CAPTURING:
    Bubbling: event goes UP (child → parent → document)
    Capturing: event goes DOWN (document → parent → child)
    
    Default is bubbling. Prevent with:
    element.addEventListener("click", handler, true); // capturing
  
  DOM TRAVERSAL:
    element.parentElement;       // parent element
    element.children;            // all child elements
    element.firstElementChild;   // first child
    element.lastElementChild;    // last child
    element.nextElementSibling;  // next sibling
    element.previousElementSibling; // previous sibling
  
  CREATING COMPLEX STRUCTURES:
    const container = document.querySelector(".container");
    
    const header = document.createElement("h1");
    header.textContent = "Title";
    header.className = "title";
    
    const list = document.createElement("ul");
    for (let i = 1; i <= 3; i++) {
      const item = document.createElement("li");
      item.textContent = `Item ${i}`;
      list.appendChild(item);
    }
    
    container.appendChild(header);
    container.appendChild(list);
  
  PERFORMANCE TIPS:
    - Use event delegation instead of many listeners
    - Cache DOM queries: const btn = document.querySelector(".btn")
    - Batch DOM modifications
    - Use innerHTML carefully (can cause security issues)

